                            <comment id="12733920" author="daijy" created="Wed, 22 Jul 2009 01:33:25 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Preliminary patch for this. Need to add unit test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12735439" author="daijy" created="Mon, 27 Jul 2009 00:44:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Include unit test&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12735688" author="daijy" created="Mon, 27 Jul 2009 19:01:43 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Modified the patch according to Alan&apos;s suggestion. It is better to use &quot;mapred.reduce.tasks&quot; mechanism to set the default parallel. &quot;default_parallel&quot; setting in Pig will map to &quot;mapred.reduce.tasks&quot; in hadoop. Now we have &quot;parallel&quot; keyword, &quot;default_parallel&quot;, and &quot;mapred.reduce.tasks&quot; to determine the number of reducers. The priority from the higher to lower is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. parallel keyword&lt;br/&gt;
2. default_parallel&lt;br/&gt;
3. &quot;mapred.reduce.tasks&quot; setting in hadoop&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The higher priority setting overrides lower priority setting. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
